modules.description: This module implements a histogram data structure for approximating distributions of floating-point values, with operations to add values, merge histograms, and compute statistical estimates. It works with histograms composed of bins, each tracking a center value and count, supporting queries like mean, standard deviation, cumulative sums, and quantile ranges. Concrete use cases include summarizing large numerical datasets, estimating percentiles in streaming data, and merging approximate distributions under memory constraints.
